Welcome to January's Turing-Roche newsletter! We hope you had a restful holiday season. Here you can find what's new in the Turing-Roche strategic partnership and opportunities, events and news from both The Alan Turing Institute and Roche.

Our [five year partnership](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FA2RdPVzwCPjQBIEbDkrPrQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C2f704cb948d64904060c08daf556986b%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638092049530604129%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=oZQku%2Bnx9TW5XN%2BrOZZ1XOR0N45TateBGhpuHmCXtjo%3D&reserved=0) was set up officially in June 2021 following a successful [Data Study Group](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FjcUQgaCS4erJRNbdckvInQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C2f704cb948d64904060c08daf556986b%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638092049530604129%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=64pg2fuzSgXOwlKnUD6Jo1jd3blkTXImZ9euUtFo%2B8I%3D&reserved=0) and a 12 week research project on lung cancer treatment. Our 'North Star' is **to enable the generation of insights to better understand patient and disease heterogeneity and its relevance to clinical outcomes at an unprecedented level of precision in order to improve clinical care. **

We will be covering multiple activities over the five years to work towards our North Star, as well as building strong connections and collaborations between the Alan Turing Institute, Roche and the wider community.

If you have anything you'd like featured in a future newsletter then please get in touch with Vicky Hellon, Community Manager for the partnership at <vhellon@turing.ac.uk>

If you would like to share this newsletter with relevant colleagues please direct them to sign-up [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FSQ5cFhBpEm41vEvtr29RdQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C2f704cb948d64904060c08daf556986b%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638092049530604129%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=C4qod8UY2O1syQRIijrkfE1ZmeWDfmxc%2FLdro9Yl74o%3D&reserved=0).

### Knowledge Share Series Event: Partnership Review and Plans for 2023

**23 January 2023**

Join us for our [partnership knowledge share series](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FfHbg9u6P3z3KbbFuJWTxaQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C2f704cb948d64904060c08daf556986b%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638092049530604129%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=2spfH5JGoDCRI8O467TCbFC5Da5GcUyBOy2GKd7OFGA%3D&reserved=0). You can catch-up on previous recordings of our events at our [YouTube channel](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FlcHiM3U_QiFc54t5XDPKBg&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C2f704cb948d64904060c08daf556986b%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638092049530760404%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=t3EKOXjNS3nzkyYN12Qhzp9bR5ly10P76fYf4nvkgMc%3D&reserved=0). ### Turing Institute Intro to Research Data Science Training Course

**Deadline for applications: 22 January 2023**

**Courses Dates: 13-24 February 2023**

Turing's Research Engineering Group (REG) are running a training course on Research Data Science. The course is open to anyone interested in learning about, or using, data science methods in research. It will help learners move beyond data science principles, to learn how to tackle real, complex and sometimes vaguely defined research data science projects. They will learn how to do this in a collaborative environment, with an emphasis on practical techniques and technologies and with an overarching awareness of ethics and diversity issues. This is an intensive, hands-on course, informed by REG's experience with research data science projects and aiming to bring learners in touch with day-to-day research data science practices. 

Find out more and how to apply [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%_%2F7hB-dRxi-5soHdl2sDB4NQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C2f704cb948d64904060c08daf556986b%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638092049530760404%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=agCCB9%2FvvEXAVWm9wuWh8mFT%2FFzpSQwRtdNigkoYZyA%3D&reserved=0).

### Course: Reproducible Machine Learning of Wearables in Health Data Science

**Deadline for applications: 20 February 2023**

**Course: 12 March 2023 to 17 March 2023**

The University of Oxford are running an immersive week-long residential post-graduate short course on reproducible machine learning of wearables datasets. This course aims to connect post-graduate and post-doctoral researchers from academia and industry with experts at Oxford's Big Data Institute and Nuffield Department of Population Health. It will cover five broad areas at the intersection of wearables, machine learning, and health data science: real world validation, time-series machine learning, reproducibility, reporting, and epidemiological considerations. Find out more and how to apply [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%_X2NsZGVlPWk1N3dkZTM2RVlnMDBpR0dJeGsxVlpEU2MzM3BZQzAyZjFjTW00dnpja25DNVR1UUJxYmktN2V5clBXQWttX0ImcmVjaXBpZW50aWQ9Y29udGFjdC00ODgwYThjMzkyM2NlYzExOGM2MjAwMjI0ODQzNGZlYi02NWEwMzBiN2EyNjM0NDlmODA5M2Y2ZjQ0YTQ4MDMzNiZlc2lkPTJlMzcyMGY5LThlOTEtZWQxMS1hYWQxLTAwMjI0ODNmNzIzMSJ9%2FnYvTczrv4uUWwZnCrt-62w&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C2f704cb948d64904060c08daf556986b%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638092049530760404%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=AGGcFx0U%2FjqxBLHi13w2OFcibIBUrGtGanmld0X%2BZjo%3D&reserved=0).

## Publication of the Month

## Combining Multi-Task Learning and Multi-Channel Variational Auto-Encoders to Exploit Datasets with Missing Observations - Application to Multi-Modal Neuroimaging Studies in Dementia

January's publication of the month is [this preprint](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FJJCVYx5KHmml5XMD6MmBFQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C2f704cb948d64904060c08daf556986b%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638092049530916659%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=vm77o5zk7z%2B6iwpJFq%2FQ8VPI40F%2B9sshdGkN7mHxfIk%3D&reserved=0) from Luigi Antelmi from the University of Côte d'Azur and colleagues. Relevant to what the partnership is exploring with our Structured Missingness research theme, the paper tackles the problem of missing information across datasets, in this case multi-modal neuroimaging studies in dementia. The authors develop a model that is able to mitigate the absence of modalities wihout having to discard any available information and simulate the model's success on synthetic data.
